msgstr "Bors Dark"

#. [unit]: type=Akladian Wonderman, id=Bors Wonder
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/25_The_Awakening.cfg:847
msgid "Bors Wonder"
msgstr "Bors Wonder"

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/25_The_Awakening.cfg:852
msgid "Curses! We are too late."
msgstr "Malédiction ! Nous arrivons trop tard."

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/25_The_Awakening.cfg:853
msgid "Should we attack, my lord?"
msgstr "Doit-on attaquer, Monseigneur ?"

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/25_The_Awakening.cfg:854
msgid ""
"No. As usual, Hoyre screwed up everything he possibly could. We will "
"withdraw to the north, and wait until Grekulak arrives to help us."
msgstr ""
"Non. Hoyre, comme à son habitude, a saboté tout ce qui était à sa portée. "
"Nous allons nous retirer vers le nord et attendre que Grekulak vienne nous "
"aider."

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/25_The_Awakening.cfg:857
msgid ""
"My king, I've heard that some of people of Wesnoth have started to take "
"revenge on their own. A few Akladian villages were massacred south of "
"Freetown. What will you do?"
msgstr ""
"Mon roi, J'ai entendu dire que des gens de Wesnoth ont commencé à se faire "
"justice eux-mêmes. Quelques villages Akladiens ont été détruits au sud de "
"Freetown. Qu'allez-vous faire ?"

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/25_The_Awakening.cfg:858
msgid "And what do you think he could do? People want revenge, so..."
msgstr ""
"Et que penses-tu qu'il puisse faire ? Les gens veulent se venger, alors..."

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/25_The_Awakening.cfg:859
msgid "Revenge on whom? On innocent woman and children?"
msgstr "Une revanche sur qui ? Des femmes et des enfants innocents ?"

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/25_The_Awakening.cfg:860
msgid ""
"Innocent? No Akladian is innocent! Even if they didn't participate in the "
"massacres, maybe their husbands or uncles did, and..."
msgstr ""
"Innocents ? Aucun Akladien n'est innocent. Même s'ils n'ont pas participé "
"aux massacres, leurs maris ou leurs oncles l'ont fait et..."

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/25_The_Awakening.cfg:861
msgid ""
"How many Wesnothians have been brought back from the dead by the killing of "
"Akladian children, Huon? I lost whole family in Freetown. But I don't want "
"to avenge them by killing families of innocent people. It will not bring "
"them back."
msgstr ""
"Combien de Wesnothiens ont été ramenés à la vie en exécutant des enfants "
"Akladiens, Huon ? J'ai perdu toute ma famille à Freetown. Mais je ne veux "
"pas me venger en tuant les familles de gens innocents. Cela ne me les "
"ramènerait pas."

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/25_The_Awakening.cfg:862
msgid ""
"You have to react, my king. If you won't stop this, Akladians with turn away "
"from you and there will be another round of civil war."
msgstr ""
"Vous devez réagir, sire. Si vous n'arrêtez pas ça, les Akladiens se "
"détourneront de vous et ce sera reparti pour un autre tour de guerre civile."

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/25_The_Awakening.cfg:863
msgid ""
"Punish them? Why? They acted out of despair and anger, they lost their whole "
"families at the hands of Akladians, how can you punish them? If you do, a "
"lot of the Wesnothians will turn away from you..."
msgstr ""
"Les punir ? Pourquoi ? Ils ont agi par désespoir et par colère, ils ont "
"perdu toute leur famille par la main des Akladiens, comment pourriez-vous "
"les punir ? Si vous le faites, beaucoup de Wesnothiens se détourneront de "
"vous..."

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/25_The_Awakening.cfg:864
msgid ""
"I now declare amnesty for everyone. But from this moment forward, anyone who "
"wants to spill innocent blood will be hunted by me and my people. People who "
"have already committed crimes should go make a pilgrimage to the Oracle to "
"ask for forgiveness."
msgstr ""
"Je déclare une amnistie pour tous. Mais dorénavant, quiconque fera couler le "
"sang innocent sera pourchassé par moi et mes gens. Ceux qui ont déjà commis "
"des crimes devraient aller en pèlerinage à la ville de l'Oracle pour "
"demander pardon."

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/25_The_Awakening.cfg:865
msgid "THIS is supposed to be a punishment? Akladians won't like it."
msgstr "C'est censé être une punition ? Les Akladiens ne vont pas aimer ça."

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/25_The_Awakening.cfg:866
msgid ""
"I am the messiah. Any Akladians who would contest my words are tools of evil "
"and will never be admitted to the land of their ancestors."
msgstr ""
"Je suis le messie. Les Akladiens qui contestent mes mots sont les "
"instruments du mal et ne seront jamais admis au pays de leurs ancêtres."

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/25_The_Awakening.cfg:867
msgid "Messiah? You do not actually believe that!?"
msgstr "Messie ? Vous ne croyez tout de même pas à ça ?"

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/25_The_Awakening.cfg:868
msgid ""
"Huon, the proper way to address your king is 'your majesty' - or at the "
"least 'my king'. Deorien was right all the time, now I see it clearly. "
"Akladians might rebel against their king and they might definitely rebel "
"against a king of mixed blood. But they cannot rebel against the hand of God "
"on earth."
msgstr ""
"Huon, la manière convenable de s'adresser à votre roi est 'votre majesté' ou "
"au moins 'mon roi'. Deorien avait raison depuis le début, maintenant, je le "
"constate. Les Akladiens peuvent se rebeller contre leur roi et bien "
"davantage contre un roi au sang mêlé. Mais ils ne peuvent pas se rebeller "
"contre la main de Dieu sur terre."

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/25_The_Awakening.cfg:869
msgid "The way to Vattin is free of enemies. Let's go."
msgstr "Pas d'ennemi en vue sur la route de Vattin. Allons-y."

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/25_The_Awakening.cfg:880
msgid "Vojta"
msgstr "Vojta"

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/25_The_Awakening.cfg:890
msgid "Kuba"
msgstr "Kuba"

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/25_The_Awakening.cfg:900
msgid "Matej"
msgstr "Matej"

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/25_The_Awakening.cfg:911
msgid "Rumpel"
msgstr "Rumpel"

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/25_The_Awakening.cfg:920
msgid "Cimper"
msgstr "Cimper"

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/25_The_Awakening.cfg:929
msgid "Camper"
msgstr "Camper"

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/25_The_Awakening.cfg:939
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/27_Orannon.cfg:1566
msgid "My king, we could really use some help here."
msgstr "Mon roi, de l'aide ne serait pas de trop ici."

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/25_The_Awakening.cfg:945
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/27_Orannon.cfg:1572
msgid ""
"We are under heavy assault, my king. We really could use some help here."
msgstr ""
"Nous subissons une attaque massive, mon roi ! Nous avons vraiment besoin "
"d'aide !"

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/25_The_Awakening.cfg:959
msgid "The barbarians attack me! I need help NOW!"
msgstr ""

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/25_The_Awakening.cfg:1020
msgid "Aaah!"
msgstr "Aaah !"

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/25_The_Awakening.cfg:1021
msgid "What? Mother, are you hurt?"
msgstr "Quoi ? Mère, vous êtes blessée ?"

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/25_The_Awakening.cfg:1022
#, fuzzy
#| msgid "No... I'm ok.. I'm ok... It was nothing."
msgid "No... I'm ok... I'm ok... It was nothing."
msgstr "Non... Ca va... Je vais bien... Ce n'était rien."

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/25_The_Awakening.cfg:1023
msgid "But what that? Are you wounded?"
msgstr "Mais, c'était quoi ? Vous êtes blessée ?"

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/25_The_Awakening.cfg:1024
msgid "No, Gawen, I've told you I'm OK!"
msgstr "Non, Gawen, je t'ai dit que ça allait !"

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/25_The_Awakening.cfg:1025
msgid ""
"The witch most likely accidentally drank a poison she was preparing for "
"someone else."
msgstr ""
"La sorcière a probablement bu par erreur un poison qu'elle avait préparé "
"pour quelqu'un d'autre."

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/25_The_Awakening.cfg:1026
msgid ""
"No, my lord. I think I know what's happening with your step-mother, but if "
"she does not want to tell you, neither will I. But be prepared... she may "
"not be able to fight in some of the battles which await us in future."
msgstr ""
"Non, Monseigneur. Je pense savoir ce qui arrive à votre belle-mère, mais si "
"elle ne veut rien vous dire, je ne le ferai pas non plus. Attendez-vous à ce "
"qu'elle... ne soit plus en mesure de participer aux batailles qui nous "
"attendent."

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/25_The_Awakening.cfg:1027
msgid ""
"Underling, be silent. You know nothing. You all know nothing. I will fight."
msgstr ""
"Silence métèque ! Tu ne sais rien ! Aucun d'entre vous ne sait ! Je vais me "
"battre !"

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/25_The_Awakening.cfg:1085
msgid "No! I haven't avenged my family!"
msgstr "Aaaargh ! Je n'ai pas vengé ma famille !"

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/25_The_Awakening.cfg:1093
msgid ""
"Stop! Don't kill me! I will give you a lot of gold if you will spare me!"
msgstr ""
"Arrêtez ! Ne me tuez pas ! Je vous donnerai plein d'or si vous m'épargnez !"

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/25_The_Awakening.cfg:1094
msgid "Were you at Freetown?"
msgstr "Étiez-vous à Freetown ?"

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/25_The_Awakening.cfg:1095
msgid "NO! That was Bor Cryne! Don't kill me!"
msgstr "NON ! C'était Bor Cryne ! Ne me tuez pas !"

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/25_The_Awakening.cfg:1096
msgid "I am an empty shell."
msgstr "Je suis une coquille vide."

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/25_The_Awakening.cfg:1102
msgid ""
"Before you will pass, I want to ask you one very simple question. Were you "
"with the Akladian army which burned Freetown?"
msgstr ""
"Avant que tu ne trépasses, je veux te poser une question toute simple. Étais-"
"tu avec l'armée Akladienne qui a brûlé Freetown ?"

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/25_The_Awakening.cfg:1103
msgid "No! No! That was Bor Cryne, I swear! I wasn't there!"
msgstr "Non ! Non ! C'était Bor Cryne, je le jure ! Je n'y étais pas !"

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/25_The_Awakening.cfg:1106
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/25_The_Awakening.cfg:1135
msgid "Well.."
msgstr "Eh bien..."

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/25_The_Awakening.cfg:1107
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/25_The_Awakening.cfg:1136
msgid "Where is Bor Cryne?"
msgstr "Où est Bor Cryne ?"

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/25_The_Awakening.cfg:1108
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/25_The_Awakening.cfg:1137
msgid "Who gave you the location of Freetown?"
msgstr "Qui a révélé la position de Freetown ?"

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/25_The_Awakening.cfg:1109
msgid "Do you know who poisoned my mother?"
msgstr "Sais-tu qui a empoisonné ma mère ?"

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/25_The_Awakening.cfg:1113
msgid "Whenever he is, he should be here instead!"
msgstr "Où qu'il soit, il devrait être ici !"

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/25_The_Awakening.cfg:1115
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/25_The_Awakening.cfg:1143
msgid "I don't know! I wasn't at Freetown, really!"
msgstr "Je ne sais pas ! Je n'étais pas à Freetown, vraiment !"

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/25_The_Awakening.cfg:1117
msgid ""
"I don't know! But Uri van Roe or Bor Cryne may know something about that..."
msgstr ""
"Je ne sais pas ! Uri van Roe ou Bor Cryne devrait savoir quelque chose à ce "
"sujet..."

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/25_The_Awakening.cfg:1130
msgid ""
"Don't kill me, Lorin! I knew you when you were a little child, I even played "
"games with you when you were small..."
msgstr ""
"Ne me tuez pas, Lorin ! Je vous ai connue alors que vous n'étiez qu'une "
"petite enfant, j'ai joué avec vous quand vous étiez petite..."

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/25_The_Awakening.cfg:1131
msgid "You should've killed me then, when you still had the chance."
msgstr ""
"Vous auriez dû me tuer à ce moment là, quand vous aviez encore une chance de "
"pouvoir le faire."

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/25_The_Awakening.cfg:1141
msgid "Whenever he is, he should be here!"
msgstr "Quoi qu'il en soit, il devrait être ici !"

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/25_The_Awakening.cfg:1157
msgid ""
"You truly are worthy to be our king! The Oracle was right! I never should "
"have listened to Hoyre...."
msgstr ""
"Vous êtes vraiment digne d'être notre roi ! L'Oracle avait raison ! Je "
"n'écouterai plus Hoyre..."

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/25_The_Awakening.cfg:1176
#, fuzzy
#| msgid "How this could be possible?"
msgid "How could this be possible?"
msgstr "Comment est-ce possible ?"

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/25_The_Awakening.cfg:1185
msgid "I should've stayed in hills in the north..."
msgstr "J'aurais dû rester dans les collines au nord..."

#. [scenario]: id=13_Scouting
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:3
msgid "Scouting"
msgstr "Exploration"

#. [part]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:21
msgid ""
"After leaving the Forest of Raedwood, Gawen and his companions found "
"themselves faced with a problem: what to do next and how to fulfill the "
"request of Mithrandil. Gawen wasn't sure what it meant to 'find the real "
"reason behind the Akladian-Orcish alliance' and definitely had no idea how "
"to accomplish that."
msgstr ""
"Après avoir quitté les bois de Raedwood, Gawen et ses compagnons se "
"retrouvèrent face à un problème : que faire ensuite pour répondre à la "
"requête de Mithrandil. Gawen ne voyait pas ce que voulait dire exactement « "
"trouver la vraie raison de l'alliance akladienne-orc » et n'avait vraiment "
"aucune idée de la manière de s'y prendre."

#. [part]
#. Spoken by Lorin
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:26
msgid ""
"I am still confused. When I saw Gawen, at first I did not recognize him. He "
"had changed from the last time I saw him. He was just a kid then, but now he "
"looks more like a young man... an amazing change in just a few months."
msgstr ""
"Je suis encore troublée. Quand j'ai vu Gawen, j'ai commencé par ne pas le "
"reconnaître. Il avait changé depuis la dernière fois où je l'avais vu. Il "
"n'était qu'un enfant alors. Là, il faisait plus jeune homme... un changement "
"étonnant en seulement quelques mois."

#. [part]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:30
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "...and now he keeps the company of underlings.... an underling child who "
#| "tries to behave like a woman, an underling man who looks like a veteran "
#| "of many battles, underling soldiers, and even worse: elves. The green "
#| "devils. But since I have been amongst underlings for months myself, this "
#| "moves me much less than I would have thought."
msgid ""
"...and now he keeps the company of underlings... an underling child who "
"tries to behave like a woman, an underling man who looks like a veteran of "
"many battles, underling soldiers, and even worse: elves. The green devils. "
"But since I have been amongst underlings for months myself, this moves me "
"much less than I would have thought."
msgstr ""
"... et maintenant il reste en compagnie de métèques... et parmi eux une "
"enfant qui essaye d'avoir l'air d'une femme, un vétéran qui avait l'air "
"d'avoir participé à de nombreuses batailles, des soldats et, encore pire, "
"des elfes. Les démons verts. Mais comme depuis des mois, j'ai vécu moi-même "
"constamment parmi des métèques, cela me trouble bien moins que je l'aurais "
"imaginé."

#. [part]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:34
msgid ""
"Looking at him, I keep on thinking about what the oracle once told me; I am "
"starting to dread those thoughts. When his father died, I thought that "
"everything - well, almost everything - the Oracle had told me were lies, but "
"now... now I am scared and I try not to think about it. But it keeps coming "
"back."
msgstr ""
"En le voyant, j'ai repensé à ce que l'oracle m'a dit un jour et soudain j'ai "
"eu peur de ces pensées. Quand son père est mort, j'ai pensé que tout — enfin "
"presque tout — ce que l'Oracle m'avait dit était faux, mais maintenant... "
"maintenant, j'ai peur et j'essaye de ne pas y songer. Mais ça revient sans "
"cesse."

#. [part]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:39
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "Gawen ordered his soldiers to march quickly to the temporary base that "
#| "had established in the plains north of Barnon. He was afraid that more "
#| "enemy forces would arrive, and wanted to tend to his wounded."
msgid ""
"Gawen ordered his soldiers to march quickly to the temporary base that had "
"been established in the plains north of Barnon. He was afraid that more "
"enemy forces would arrive, and wanted to tend to his wounded."
msgstr ""
"Gawen ordonna à ses soldats de marcher rapidement vers la base temporaire "
"qu'il avait établie dans les plaines au nord de Barnon. Il craignait "
"l'arrivée d'autres forces ennemies et il voulait prendre soin des blessés."

#. [part]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:43
msgid ""
"Fighting in the swamps of Saorduc had not made anyone happy and Gawen's "
"soldiers were delighted to leave the frozen fens. They were all mired in a "
"strange mix of mud and snow, and this was not improving their mood."
msgstr ""
"Combattre dans les marais de Saorduc n'avait fait plaisir à personne et les "
"soldats de Gawen se félicitaient de pouvoir quitter les terres gelées. Ils "
"étaient tous embourbés dans un mélange de boue et de neige ce qui "
"n'améliorait en rien leur humeur."

#. [part]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:47
msgid ""
"After seeing the atrocities committed by the orcs, Gawen's soldiers were "
"unusually silent. None joked nor sang, as had been the norm after their last "
"few battles. Each seemed to be thinking about their own families, their "
"wives and children."
msgstr ""
"Après avoir vu les atrocités commises par les orcs, les soldats de Gawen "
"étaient inhabituellement silencieux. Aucun ne blaguait ou ne chantait, comme "
"ils en avaient l'habitude au sortir des précédentes batailles. Ils "
"semblaient tous penser à leurs familles, leurs femmes et leurs enfants."

#. [part]
#. Spoken by Reme Carrenemoe
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:53
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "I am finally free! I still can hardly believe it. Not only am I free, but "
#| "also Gawen, my king, is alive. It is a very real relief for me; the "
#| "thought that I had abandoned him during th Battle of Barnon has haunted "
#| "me for weeks now."
msgid ""
"I am finally free! I still can hardly believe it. Not only am I free, but "
"also Gawen, my king, is alive. It is a very real relief for me; the thought "
"that I had abandoned him during the Battle of Barnon has haunted me for "
"weeks now."
msgstr ""
"Je suis enfin libre ! Je peux difficilement le croire. Non seulement je suis "
"libre, mais Gawen, mon roi, est vivant. C'est un grand soulagement pour "
"moi ; l'idée que je l'avais abandonné sur la bataille de Barnon me hantait "
"depuis des semaines."

#. [part]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:58
msgid ""
"I am surprised that he is surrounded by Underlings. But then, Gawen has "
"demanded that I should never use that word again, that I should start to "
"think of them as 'Wesnothians'. I think the girl with red hair has a crush "
"on Gawen, and despite Lorin calling her 'a mite of a child' she is a woman "
"already, and quite pretty."
msgstr ""
"Je suis surpris de le voir entouré de Métèques. Mais maintenant, Gawen m'a "
"demandé de ne plus utiliser ce mot, et de commencer à penser à eux comme à "
"des Wesnothiens. Je pense que la fille aux cheveux rouges a un petit "
"sentiment pour Gawen et même si Lorin l'appelle « gamine teigneuse », c'est "
"déjà une femme, plutôt jolie d'ailleurs."

#. [part]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:62
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "I am surprised that he is surrounded by Underlings. But then, Gawen has "
#| "demanded that I should never use that word again, that I should start to "
#| "think of them as 'Wesnothians'. I think the girl with red hair has a "
#| "crush on Gawen, and despite Lorin calling her 'a mite of a child' she is "
#| "a woman already, and quite pretty."
msgid ""
"I am surprised that he is surrounded by Underlings. But then, Gawen has "
"demanded that I should never use that word again, that I should start to "
"think of them as 'Wesnothians'. I think the girl with red hair has a crush "
"on Gawen, and despite her youth, she is a woman already, and quite pretty."
msgstr ""
"Je suis surpris de le voir entouré de Métèques. Mais maintenant, Gawen m'a "
"demandé de ne plus utiliser ce mot, et de commencer à penser à eux comme à "
"des Wesnothiens. Je pense que la fille aux cheveux rouges a un petit "
"sentiment pour Gawen et même si Lorin l'appelle « gamine teigneuse », c'est "
"déjà une femme, plutôt jolie d'ailleurs."

#. [part]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:67
msgid ""
"Failing to save Reme left Gawen feeling devastated. The news about Reme's "
"death reached Gawen's temporary base soon after, throwing all into a somber "
"melancholy."
msgstr ""
"Échouer à sauver Reme  eut un effet dévastateur sur le moral de Gawen. La "
"nouvelle de la mort de Reme parvint peu après à la base temporaire de Gawen, "
"le plongeant dans une sombre mélancolie."

#. [part]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:82
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:88
msgid ""
"Bitter and depressed, having failed to interrogate a single orc leader who "
"knew anything of substance, Gawen and his troops headed home toward "
"Freetown. Along the way, they found a near-frozen orc, dying in the snow. "
"'Grekulak', it said, and then expired."
msgstr ""
"Amers et déprimés, n'ayant pas réussi à interroger un seul chef orc qui "
"sache quelque chose de substantiel, Gawen et ses troupes se replièrent vers "
"Freetown. Sur le chemin, ils trouvèrent un orc presque complètement gelé et "
"mourant dans la neige. Il dit simplement « Grekulak » et expira."

#. [part]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:102
msgid ""
"Rob Roe was not amongst Gawen's soldiers. He disappeared one night and no "
"one, not even the outlaws in Gawen's army, knew the reasons of Roe's sudden "
"disappearance. Outlaws were startled by the event and many of them refused "
"to follow Gawen's orders any more."
msgstr ""
"Rob Roe n'était pas parmi les soldats de Gawen. Il avait disparu une nuit et "
"personne, pas même les brigands de l'armée de Gawen, ne savait pourquoi. Les "
"brigands en furent déroutés et beaucoup d'entre eux refusèrent d'obéir plus "
"longtemps aux ordres de Gawen."

#. [scenario]: id=13_Scouting
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:112
msgid ""
"I've seen a lot of orcs lately. They are going here and there, and have been "
"surprisingly disciplined and well-behaved considering what I've heard about "
"orcs. Well, yes, they killed and ate three of our cows and took our only "
"horse, but that's what one can expect from any soldiers. Some orcish unit is "
"garrisoned near Barnon, south from here."
msgstr ""
"J'ai vu des tas d'orcs récemment. Ils vont et viennent, étrangement bien "
"disciplinés et se comportant bien mieux qu'à leur ordinaire. Bien sûr, ils "
"ont tué et mangé trois de nos vaches et pris notre unique cheval, mais c'est "
"le comportement normal de n'importe quel soldat. Quelques unités sont en "
"garnison près de Barnon, au sud d'ici."

#. [scenario]: id=13_Scouting
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:114
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:211
msgid "Reme? No, I have not heard about him."
msgstr "Reme ? Non je n'ai pas entendu parler de lui."

#. [scenario]: id=13_Scouting
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:117
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "Bontom? of course I know about it. It is a nice place a little bit west "
#| "from here! My wife is from that area."
msgid ""
"Bontom? Of course I know about it. It is a nice place a little bit west from "
"here! My wife is from that area."
msgstr ""
"Bontom ? Bien sûr que je connais. C'est un bel endroit un peu à l'ouest "
"d'ici ! Ma femme est originaire de cette région."

#. [scenario]: id=13_Scouting
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:150
msgid "No offense, but you've already asked me that question."
msgstr "Ne le prenez pas mal, mais vous m'avez déjà posé cette question."

#. [scenario]: id=13_Scouting
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:153
msgid "Well, and what do you propose in exchange?"
msgstr "Bien et que proposez-vous en échange ?"

#. [scenario]: id=13_Scouting
#. [message]: speaker=Lady Lorin
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:154
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/09_Hired_Swords.cfg:503
msgid "What about this:"
msgstr "Que penses-tu de ça :"

#. [scenario]: id=13_Scouting
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:155
msgid "If not, I will burn down this village."
msgstr "Sinon, je brûle tout le village."

