#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:598
msgid "Anything for you, young knight."
msgstr "Tout ce que vous voudrez, jeune chevalier."

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:631
msgid "Free men from Raedwood forest! You are always welcome here."
msgstr ""
"Hommes libres des forêts de Raedwood ! Vous êtes toujours les bienvenus ici."

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:673
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:682
msgid "Yahyazad"
msgstr "Yahyazad"

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:709
msgid "Where Reme Carrenemoe could possibly be?"
msgstr "Où Reme Carrenmoe pourrait-il bien être ?"

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:710
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/18_Start_of_the_Quest.cfg:576
msgid "Advise me what could we do now."
msgstr "Conseille-moi sur ce qu'on pourrait faire maintenant."

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:711
msgid "Tell me about my mother."
msgstr "Parle-moi de ma mère."

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:716
msgid "You are joking, right? He is in our camp!"
msgstr "Tu veux rire n'est-ce pas ? Il est dans notre camp !"

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:718
msgid "Probably still in that Bontom place the peasants told us about."
msgstr "Probablement toujours à ce Bontom dont les paysans nous ont parlé."

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:720
msgid "In some place called Bontom. We could ask peasants about it."
msgstr ""
"Dans un endroit nommé Bontom. Vous pouvez interroger les paysans à ce sujet."

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:722
msgid "I have no idea where your friend may be."
msgstr "Je ne sais pas du tout où votre ami peut se trouver."

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:729
msgid "About your mother? What do you want to know about her?"
msgstr "Ta mère ? Que veux-tu savoir à son sujet ?"

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:730
msgid "Everything."
msgstr "Tout."

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:731
msgid ""
"Well, she was from a royal house. The Akladian king gave her a simple "
"choice: marry him or he would unleash his anger on her family. So, she "
"agreed. I visited her from time to time, singing songs, bringing her news "
"from home... "
msgstr ""
"En fait, elle était issue d'une maison royale. Le roi Akladien ne lui laissa "
"guère le choix. Si elle ne l'épousait pas, il déchaînerait sa colère contre "
"sa famille, elle accepta donc la proposition. Je lui rendais visite de temps "
"à autre, nous chantions des chansons, je lui donnais des nouvelles de son "
"pays..."

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:732
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "I think eventually she even warmed to your father, the king. When she "
#| "gave birth to you, she gave everything she had for you. But behind her "
#| "back Akladian clans were conspiring... and finally someone gave her a "
#| "poisoned cup. She died, slowly, and painfully. I was able to be near her "
#| "in her final hours. I promised her that I would take care of you."
msgid ""
"I think eventually she even warmed up to your father, the king. When she "
"gave birth to you, she gave everything she had for you. But behind her back "
"Akladian clans were conspiring... and finally someone gave her a poisoned "
"cup. She died, slowly, and painfully. I was able to be near her in her final "
"hours. I promised her that I would take care of you."
msgstr ""
"Je pense qu'elle avait même commencé à apprécier le roi, votre père. Quand "
"tu es né, elle a fait tout ce qu'elle pouvait pour toi. Mais les clans "
"Akladiens conspiraient dans son dos... finalement, on l'empoisonna. Elle est "
"morte, d'une lente et pénible agonie. Je pus rester près d'elle jusqu'à la "
"fin. Je lui promis de m'occuper de toi."

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:733
msgid "Who poisoned her?"
msgstr "Qui l'a empoisonnée ?"

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:734
msgid "I don't know. No one knows."
msgstr "Je ne sais pas. Personne ne sait."

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:736
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "Rob Roe mentioned Lorin clan once bought some special poison from "
#| "Outlaws... "
msgid ""
"Rob Roe mentioned Lorin's clan once bought some special poison from "
"Outlaws... "
msgstr ""
"Rob Roe a dit une fois que le clan de Lorin avait acheté un poison spécial "
"aux hors-la-loi..."

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:737
msgid "And you think that..."
msgstr "Et tu penses que..."

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:738
msgid "Why shouldn't I think that?"
msgstr "Pourquoi ne le penserais-je pas ?"

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:739
msgid ""
"You are right, Gawen. Akladians have a long history of poisoning each other. "
"You might say it's their national sport. But still... yes, it had escaped my "
"attention before."
msgstr ""
"Tu as raison, Gawen. Les Akladiens s'empoisonnent constamment. On pourrait "
"dire que c'est leur sport national. Mais, en effet, cela avait échappé à mon "
"attention jusqu'ici."

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:744
msgid "Hey Karen, what's up?"
msgstr "Hé, Karen, quoi de neuf ?"

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:745
msgid "I just made up a new song about you, want to hear it?"
msgstr ""
"Je viens juste d'écrire une nouvelle chanson pour toi. Tu veux l'entendre ?"

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:746
msgid "You are a gifted girl... fighting, singing, what else can you do?"
msgstr ""
"Tu es une jeune fille douée... se battre, chanter, que sais-tu faire "
"d'autre ?"

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:747
msgid ""
"I can also dance. Gawen. When we return to Freetown I could dance for you... "
msgstr ""
"Je sais aussi danser, Gawen. Quand nous retournerons à Freetown, je pourrais "
"danser pour toi..."

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:748
msgid "I'm sure I would enjoy watching you dance."
msgstr "Je suis sûr que j'aimerai ça."

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:749
msgid "Oh, I bet you would!"
msgstr "Je parie que oui !"

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:751
msgid ""
"Thank you, Gawen, once again. You have saved my life. I will never forget "
"it, and I will never be able to repay my debt. Earlier my life belonged to "
"you because of duty; now it is yours by choice."
msgstr ""
"Je vous remercie, Gawen, une fois de plus. Vous avez sauvé ma vie. Je ne "
"l'oublierai jamais, et je ne serai jamais en mesure de rembourser ma dette. "
"Avant, ma vie vous appartenait à cause de mon devoir. Maintenant, elle vous "
"appartient par mon propre choix."

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:753
msgid "Gaumhaldric, an interesting mother you have. Can I ask you a question?"
msgstr ""
"Gaumhaldric, vous avez une mère intéressante. Est-ce que je peux vous poser "
"une question ?"

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:754
msgid "Sure, go ahead."
msgstr "Bien sûr, allez-y."

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:755
msgid ""
"Is she spoken for? I mean, is there someone she loves? I have often noticed "
"her gazing up at the sky, far, far away, as if she were thinking about "
"someone... or something."
msgstr ""
"Est-ce qu'elle est engagée ? Je veux dire, est-ce qu'elle aime quelqu'un ? "
"J'ai remarqué qu'elle regardait le ciel, très très loin parfois, comme si "
"elle pensait à quelqu'un, ou à quelque chose."

#. [event]
#. this is just Gawen's assumption; my own assumption is that she is thinking about what the Oracle told her:
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:757
msgid ""
"I think she must be remembering my father. She has no one else I know about."
msgstr ""
"Je suppose qu'elle se rappelle mon père. À ma connaissance, elle n'a "
"personne d'autre."

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:758
msgid ""
"That is fortunate for me. She seems to have locked her heart up in an "
"unbreakable fortress... but I think I can find a way into her heart. With "
"time and patience, I'm sure I can discover a way to break down those walls. "
msgstr ""
"C'est heureux pour moi. Elle a l'air d'avoir enfermé son cœur dans une "
"forteresse imprenable... mais je crois que je peux en trouver le chemin. "
"Avec du temps et de la patience, je suis certain de pouvoir découvrir le "
"moyen de jeter bas ces murs."

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:759
msgid ""
"Majid Yahyazad, Lorin is my step-mother, but she has never really shown any "
"tenderness, even to me. I have always known her to be a harsh and "
"unforgiving woman."
msgstr ""
"Majid Yahyazad, Lorin est ma belle-mère, mais elle ne n'a jamais montré de "
"tendresse envers quiconque, même pas moi. Je l'ai toujours connue brutale et "
"impitoyable."

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:760
msgid ""
"I'm afraid pursuing her will come with a heavy price. I think she thinks "
"love is a weakness... she seems more interested in war and finding new ways "
"to cause pain to others."
msgstr ""
"J'ai bien peur que la courtiser ne vous coûte très cher. Je crois qu'elle "
"pense que l'amour est une faiblesse... elle paraît plus intéressée par la "
"guerre et la découverte de nouveaux moyens de faire souffrir autrui."

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:761
msgid ""
"Ah, Gaumhaldric, perhaps you are right, but if it will be as a war to unlock "
"her heart, I am prepared to wage it. I am well-acquainted with the ways of "
"war."
msgstr ""
"Ah, Gaumhaldric, peut-être avez-vous raison, mais si forcer son cœur "
"s'apparente à une guerre, alors je suis prêt à la livrer. Je suis assez "
"compétent en ce qui concerne la guerre."

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:762
msgid ""
"Besides, in the end, the war for the affection of a worthy woman is the only "
"war where the price to win is a privilege, not a burden, to pay."
msgstr ""
"D'une autre côté, finalement, la bataille pour gagner l'affection d'une "
"femme de qualité est la seule guerre où l'effort à consentir est un "
"privilège et non une fatigue."

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:763
msgid "You find my step-mother... a worthy challenge, then? "
msgstr "Vous trouvez donc que ma marâtre... est un défi qui en vaut la peine ?"

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:764
msgid "I do... and shall gladly pay the price to try to win her heart. "
msgstr ""
"Certainement... et je paierai volontiers le prix qu'il faudra pour gagner "
"son cœur."

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:765
msgid ""
"You have my blessing, noble Majid, for what it's worth. Sometimes the "
"ruthlessness of the 'She-Wolf of Haeltin' still scares even me. "
msgstr ""
"Vous avez ma bénédiction, noble Majid, pour autant que ça vaille quelque "
"chose. Parfois, la rudesse de la « Louve de Haetlin » m'effraie moi-même."

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:770
msgid "Mother, may I have a word with you?"
msgstr "Mère, est-ce qu'on peut discuter un instant ?"

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:771
msgid "Your clan once bought poison from outlaws. Why?"
msgstr "Votre clan a acheté du poison aux hors-la-loi. Pourquoi ?"

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:772
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:780
msgid "What do you think about Yahyazad?"
msgstr "Que pensez-vous d'Yahyazad ?"

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:773
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:781
msgid "What do you know about orcs?"
msgstr "Que savez-vous au sujet des orcs ?"

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:774
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:782
msgid "How did my real mother die?"
msgstr "Comment ma vraie mère est-elle morte ?"

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:788
msgid "Why do you ask?"
msgstr "Pourquoi demandes-tu ça ?"

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:789
msgid "Well, he seems to be interested in you."
msgstr "Eh bien, il semble s'intéresser à vous."

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:790
msgid ""
"Yes, I noticed that. I think one would have to be blind NOT to notice that. "
"But I am not interested in him."
msgstr ""
"Oui, je l'ai remarqué. Il faudrait être aveugle pour ne PAS le remarquer. "
"Mais il ne m'intéresse pas."

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:791
msgid "Why not? He seems to be a good man."
msgstr "Pourquoi ? Il a l'air d'être un homme de bien."

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:792
msgid "He is an underling."
msgstr "C'est un métèque."

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:793
msgid ""
"Underling? Mother, why do you still use such words? I am 'underling' too, "
"after all."
msgstr ""
"Métèque ? Mère, pourquoi utiliser de tels mots ? Je suis moi aussi un "
"métèque, après tout."

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:794
msgid ""
"No! I could never call you that. You are not... I mean... I... oh, you are "
"too young to understand!"
msgstr ""
"Non. Je ne t'appellerais jamais comme ça. Tu n'es pas... Je veux dire... "
"Je... Ah, tu es trop jeune pour comprendre !"

#. [event]
#. cross-reference to dialogue in S16, Choosing the Best:
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:796
msgid ""
"Besides, you have lost your memory, so you probably do not remember what our "
"customs are regarding widows that betray their dead husbands. I will explain "
"it to you another time."
msgstr ""
"D'ailleurs, tu as perdu la mémoire, tu as donc probablement dû oublier aussi "
"nos coutumes à propos des veuves qui trahissent leur mari défunt. Je "
"t'expliquerai ça une autre fois."

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:798
msgid ""
"Orcs? They are good fighters. Strong, disciplined, I wish I had such "
"soldiers."
msgstr ""
"Les orcs. Ce sont de bons combattants. Forts, disciplinés, je souhaiterais "
"avoir de tels soldats."

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:799
msgid ""
"Mother, orcs just burn, pillage, and murder! They hate us, and yet you seem "
"to respect them?!?"
msgstr ""
"Mères, les orcs incendient, pillent, et tuent ! ils nous détestent et vous "
"semblez les respecter ?!?"

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:800
msgid ""
"Well, we are burning, pillaging, murdering and hate our enemies too. What's "
"the difference?"
msgstr ""
"Et bien, nous incendions, pillons, tuons et détestons aussi nos ennemis. Où "
"est la différence ?"

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:802
msgid "Poison? What poison? My clan has never bought any poison!"
msgstr "Du poison ? Quel poison ? Mon clan n'a jamais acheté de poison !"

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:803
msgid "Rob Roe told me about it."
msgstr "Rob Roe me l'a dit."

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:804
msgid ""
"Can you repeat that name? Rob - Roe. Rob Roe... No, I can't say I remember "
"that name. I don't know anything about my clan buying a poison. But then, I "
"am only a woman, and our clan lord didn't tell me everything."
msgstr ""
"Répète un peu ce nom ? Rob — Roe. Rob Roe... Non, ça ne me rappelle rien. En "
"fait, je n'ai jamais entendu dire que mon clan avait acheté du poison. Mais "
"je ne suis qu'une femme, et notre chef de clan ne me disait pas tout."

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:807
#, fuzzy
#| msgid "Your mother? Your.. why you are asking ME about your mother?"
msgid "Your mother? Your... why you are asking ME about your mother?"
msgstr ""
"Ta mère ? Ta... pourquoi me demandes-tu à MOI de te parler de ta mère ?"

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:808
msgid ""
"I can't remember anything about her. I would love to hear something about "
"her. Did you know her?"
msgstr ""
"Je ne me rappelle de rien à son sujet. J'aurais voulu en savoir un peu plus. "
"Vous l'avez connue ?"

#. [event]
#. this is a Suspiciously Specific Denial: https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SuspiciouslySpecificDenial
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:810
msgid ""
"No! I did not know her! I... I'm sorry Gawen, but I don't know how your "
"mother died or who poisoned her."
msgstr ""
"Non ! je ne l'ai pas connue ! Je.. Je suis désolé Gawen, mais je ne sais pas "
"comment elle est morte ni qui l'a empoisonnée."

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:811
msgid "I wasn't asking you about that."
msgstr "Ce n'est pas ce que je vous demandais."

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:828
msgid "There are no more orcs near this ruins of the village."
msgstr "Il n'y a plus d'orcs autour des ruines de ce village."

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:831
msgid ""
"My lord! This time for sure you will chase off that orcish band, kill all "
"the orcs, and free my people!"
msgstr ""
"Monseigneur ! Cette fois, je suis sûr que cette fois vous allez poursuivre "
"cette bande d'orcs, les tuer tous et libérer mon peuple !"

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:833
msgid "So, should we take on the orcs?"
msgstr "Donc, allons-nous régler la question de ces orcs ?"

#. [unit]: type=Peasant, id=Matthews Eagle Eye
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:845
msgid "Matthews Eagle Eye"
msgstr "Matthews Oeil-d'Aigle"

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:854
msgid "Someone is hiding here!"
msgstr "Quelqu'un se cache ici !"

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:856
msgid "Ah! Humans! And Akladians with them?! Still, what good fortune!"
msgstr ""
"Ah ! Des humains ! Et des Akladiens avec eux ?! Peu importe, quelle chance !"

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:858
msgid "Ah! Humans! And not Akladians! What good fortune!"
msgstr "Ah ! Des humains ! Et pas d'Akladiens ! Quelle chance !"

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:860
msgid "Who are you, and what are you doing here?"
msgstr "Qui êtes-vous ? Et que faites-vous ici ?"

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:861
msgid ""
"The orcs burned down my village, Ruen, and they left not long ago. They took "
"many prisoners. I was hiding here, waiting for a miracle. And now the "
"miracle has come!"
msgstr ""
"Les orcs ont brûlé mon village, Ruen. Il n'y a pas longtemps qu'ils sont "
"partis. Ils ont fait de nombreux prisonniers. Je me cachais là en espérant "
"un miracle et le miracle est arrivé !"

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:862
msgid ""
"Oh my. It's so funny I think I'm gonna die laughing. Gaumhaldric the Miracle-"
"maker, how about the sound of that?"
msgstr ""
"Mon Dieu, c'est si drôle ! Je crois que je vais en mourir de rire. "
"Gaumhaldric, le faiseur de miracles. Qu'en dites-vous ?"

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:863
msgid "Miracle? What do you mean?"
msgstr "Un miracle ? Que voulez-vous dire ?"

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:864
msgid ""
"You of course will chase that orcish band, kill all the orcs and free my "
"people!"
msgstr ""
"Vous allez poursuivre ces orcs, les tuer et libérer mon peuple, bien sûr !"

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:866
msgid "Hm, my lord, do you think we should fullfill this peasant's request?"
msgstr ""
"Hum, Monseigneur, pensez-vous que nous devrions répondre à la requête des "
"paysans ?"

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:873
msgid "Well, I hope it's wise decision."
msgstr "Bien, j'espère que c'est une sage décision."

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:874
msgid ""
"Of course it is. We are searching for orcs, and those are orcs, isn't it?"
msgstr ""
"Évidemment ! Nous cherchions des orcs, et ce sont des orcs, n'est-ce pas ?"

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:877
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:905
msgid "Yes, on other hand maybe we should search elsewhere."
msgstr "Oui, d'un autre côté, on devrait peut-être chercher ailleurs."

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:888
msgid "We already fought with outlaws from Bontom, my lord."
msgstr "Nous avons déjà combattu les hors-la-loi de Bontom, Monseigneur."

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:897
msgid "So, should we go into Bontom?"
msgstr "Alors, devrions-nous aller à Bontom ?"

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/13_Scouting.cfg:902
msgid "Yes, we should save Reme now."
msgstr "Oui, maintenant, nous devons sauver Reme."

#. [scenario]: id=15a_The_Preparations
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/15a_The_Preparations.cfg:3
msgid "The Preparations"
msgstr "Les Préparatifs"

#. [part]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/15a_The_Preparations.cfg:18
msgid ""
"A few days passed. Finally, the Freetown council decided to send Gawen to "
"search for Deorien. Gwidle Turlin came to Gawen to ask for his assent."
msgstr ""
"Quelques jours passèrent. Finalement, le conseil de Freetown décida "
"d'envoyer Gawen à la recherche de Deorien. Gwidle Turlin vint voir Gawen "
"pour lui demander son accord."

#. [label]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/15a_The_Preparations.cfg:26
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/15_Back_in_Freetown.cfg:39
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/11_Council_in_Freetown.cfg:26
msgid "Freetown"
msgstr "Freetown"

#. [side]: id=Gwidle Turlin, type=General
