#. "teach an old dog new tricks" is a common idiom in English; feel free to word your translation with a similar
#. idiom from your own language, as long as it allows Lorin to react to the "old" part in her response:
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/14b_Bontom.cfg:646
msgid "Gawen, she is Akladian. You can't teach an old dog new tricks."
msgstr ""
"Gawen, c'est une Akladienne. Ce n'est pas à un vieux singe qu'on apprend à "
"faire des grimaces."

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/14b_Bontom.cfg:647
msgid "Who are you calling OLD?!"
msgstr "QUI traitez-vous de VIEUX ?!"

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/14b_Bontom.cfg:652
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "You were good opponent. What is your name, please tell me, so I can tell "
#| "the spirits of ancestors who defeated me?"
msgid ""
"You were a good opponent. What is your name? Please tell me, so I can tell "
"the spirits of my ancestors who defeated me!"
msgstr ""
"Tu as été un grand adversaire. Dis-moi quel est ton nom, que je puisse dire "
"aux esprits des ancêtres qui m'a abattu !"

#. [event]
#. Gawen was about to give him his fake "Gaumhaldric" name before changing his mind and deciding to use his real one:
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/14b_Bontom.cfg:654
#, fuzzy
#| msgid "Gau.. Gawen. Gawen Hagarthen."
msgid "Gau... Gawen. Gawen Hagarthen."
msgstr "Gau.. Gawen. Gawen Hagarthen."

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/14b_Bontom.cfg:655
msgid ""
"My king! Now I know why I was defeated. This is my punishment for betrayal. "
"I should never have listened to the orders of our clan leaders. My king, "
"will you forgive me?"
msgstr ""
"Mon roi ! Maintenant je sais pourquoi j'ai été battu. C'est la punition de "
"ma trahison. Je n'aurais jamais dû suivre les ordres du chef de notre clan. "
"Mon roi, me pardonnerez-vous ?"

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/14b_Bontom.cfg:656
msgid "Lie in peace, soldier."
msgstr "Repose en paix, soldat."

#. [event]
#. this is a well-known quote from a well-known book -- translators, please find how this quote was translated into your language before trying translating it by yourself.
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/14b_Bontom.cfg:663
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "I must not Fear. Fear is the mind-killer. Fear is little death that "
#| "brings total obliteration. I will let it pass through me and over me. "
#| "Where the fear has gone there will be nothing. Only I will remain."
msgid ""
"I must not fear. Fear is the mind-killer. Fear is the little-death that "
"brings total obliteration. I will face my fear. I will permit it to pass "
"over me and through me. And when it has gone past I will turn the inner eye "
"to see its path. Where the fear has gone there will be nothing. Only I will "
"remain."
msgstr ""
"Je ne dois pas avoir peur. La peur tue l'esprit. La peur est une petite mort "
"qui amène l'effacement complet. Je la laisserai pas passer à travers moi. Là "
"où la peur s'en est allée, il ne restera rien. Rien sauf moi."

#. [event]
#. this is a play on what the orc just said; try to use similar wording when translating:
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/14b_Bontom.cfg:665
msgid ""
"Oh that was cute. Now, if you are quite finished, I have here this little "
"knife-thing. This knife is what brings total obliteration, not to mention "
"suffering."
msgstr ""
"Oh, que c'était mignon. Maintenant, si tu as fini, J'ai cette petite chose "
"coupante. Ce couteau est ce qui amène l'effacement total, sans parler de la "
"souffrance."

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/14b_Bontom.cfg:666
msgid "I must not... ARGH!... I must not..."
msgstr "Je ne dois pas... ARGH !... Je ne dois pas..."

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/14b_Bontom.cfg:667
#, fuzzy
#| msgid "Why you are here, allied with traitors from Akladian race?"
msgid "Why are you here, allied with traitors from the Akladian race?"
msgstr "Pourquoi es-tu ici, allié aux traîtres akladiens ?"

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/14b_Bontom.cfg:668
msgid ""
"I know nothing! I know nothing! Our guide Grekulak ordered us to ally with "
"Akladians, I know nothing more!"
msgstr ""
"Je ne sais rien ! Je ne sais rien ! Notre guide Grekulak nous a ordonné de "
"nous allier aux Akladiens. Je ne sais rien de plus."

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/14b_Bontom.cfg:671
msgid "Mother, you may let him go now."
msgstr "Mère, vous pouvez le laisser aller maintenant."

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/14b_Bontom.cfg:672
msgid "Argh!"
msgstr "Argh !"

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/14b_Bontom.cfg:678
msgid ""
"Excuse me, my son, this orc screamed so loud in agony that I couldn't hear "
"what you were saying. What was that?"
msgstr ""
"Excuse-moi, mon fils, cet orc a crié si fort durant son agonie que je n'ai "
"pas entendu ce que tu disais. Tu veux répéter ?"

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/14b_Bontom.cfg:679
msgid "Never mind. My step-mother is obsessed with death and pain. Sigh."
msgstr ""
"N'y pensons plus. Ma belle-mère est obsédée par la mort et la souffrance. On "
"n'y peut rien."

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/14b_Bontom.cfg:680
msgid "And she looks beautiful in armour, too."
msgstr "Et elle est si belle en armure."

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/14b_Bontom.cfg:724
msgid "Ha! The outlaws were hiding some gold here!"
msgstr "Ah ! Les hors-la-loi avaient caché de l'or ici !"

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/14b_Bontom.cfg:725
#, fuzzy
#| msgid "You have received 20 gold pieces"
msgid "You have received $outlaw_gold_amt gold pieces."
msgstr "Vous avez reçu 20 pièces d'or."

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/14b_Bontom.cfg:741
msgid "Ha! The Akladians were hiding some gold here!"
msgstr "Ah ! Les Akladiens avaient caché de l'or ici !"

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/14b_Bontom.cfg:742
#, fuzzy
#| msgid "You have received 20 gold pieces"
msgid "You have received $akl_gold_amt gold pieces."
msgstr "Vous avez reçu 20 pièces d'or."

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/14b_Bontom.cfg:747
msgid "I guess this was gold prepared to pay for Reme Carrenemoe."
msgstr ""
"Je suppose que cet or devait servir à payer la capture de Reme Carrenemoe."

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/14b_Bontom.cfg:897
msgid "The outlaws are defeated!"
msgstr ""

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/14b_Bontom.cfg:932
msgid ""
"Akladian? Go away. Since the death of my old man I do not talk to Akladians."
msgstr ""
"Akladien ? Passez votre chemin. Depuis la mort de mon vieux mari, je ne "
"parle plus aux Akladiens."

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/14b_Bontom.cfg:937
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/14b_Bontom.cfg:972
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "What do you want? I have already teached one of your people how to cure. "
#| "That should be enough."
msgid ""
"What do you want? I have already taught one of your people how to cure. That "
"should be enough."
msgstr ""
"Qu'est-ce que vous voulez ? J'ai déjà montré comment soigner à quelqu'un de "
"votre peuple. Cela devrait suffire."

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/14b_Bontom.cfg:939
msgid ""
"What do you want? I have already told you I speak to no Akladians since my "
"husband, poor old soul, have died."
msgstr ""
"Qu'est-ce que vous voulez ? Je vous ai déjà dit que je ne parlais plus aux "
"Akladiens depuis la mort de mon mari, le pauvre homme."

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/14b_Bontom.cfg:974
msgid "Ooo, who's there? The avengers from Freetown on a mission, huh?"
msgstr "Ooh, qui est là ? Les vengeurs de Freetown en mission, hein ?"

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/14b_Bontom.cfg:976
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/14b_Bontom.cfg:979
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/14b_Bontom.cfg:981
msgid ""
"Yes, old woman, we are from Freetown. You can go back to your village, you "
"are safe now."
msgstr ""
"Oui, la vieille, nous sommes de Freetown. Vous pouvez rentrer chez vous au "
"village maintenant, vous êtes en sécurité maintenant."

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/14b_Bontom.cfg:983
msgid ""
"Ha, ha, ha. Indeed I am, since it seems to me you are taking care of orcs "
"and Akladians. You know what, young fellow: in exchange for what you did for "
"this poor village, I will teach you few tricks about herbs."
msgstr ""
"Ha, ha, ha. Je le suis en effet, du moment que vous vous occupez des orcs et "
"des Akladiens. Tu sais quoi, jeune homme : en échange de ce que tu as fait "
"pour ce pauvre village, je vais t'apprendre quelques trucs avec des herbes."

#. [scenario]: id=15_Back_in_Freetown
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/15_Back_in_Freetown.cfg:3
msgid "Back in Freetown"
msgstr "Retour à Freetown."

#. [part]
#. spoken by Gawen
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/15_Back_in_Freetown.cfg:16
msgid ""
"The winter was just ending when we returned to Freetown. Soldiers were "
"singing mirthful songs, waiting impatiently for the chance to see the faces "
"of their wives and children again. "
msgstr ""
"L'hiver finissait juste alors quand nous sommes retournés à Freetown. Les "
"soldats chantaient des airs joyeux, dans l'heureuse perspective de revoir "
"leur femme et leurs enfants."

#. [part]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/15_Back_in_Freetown.cfg:19
msgid ""
"Even Lorin and Karen seemed to finally be getting along. I thought they "
"might have started to like each other. Karen had even promised to show Lorin "
"a few easy exercises to help her to regain the slenderness of her youth."
msgstr ""
"Même Lorin et Karen semblaient finalement mieux s'entendre. Je pense "
"qu'elles commençaient à s'apprécier mutuellement. Karen avait même promis à "
"Lorin de lui montrer quelques exercices faciles qui lui permettraient de "
"retrouver la souplesse de sa jeunesse."

#. [part]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/15_Back_in_Freetown.cfg:25
msgid ""
"Rob Roe disappeared one night and no one, not even the outlaws in my army, "
"knew the reasons of Roe's sudden disappearance. Outlaws were startled by the "
"event and many of them refused to follow my orders any more."
msgstr ""
"Rob Roe disparut une nuit et personne, pas même les brigands de mon armée, "
"ne savait pourquoi. Les brigands furent déroutés et pour la plupart, "
"refusèrent d'obéir plus longtemps à mes ordres."

#. [part]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/15_Back_in_Freetown.cfg:30
msgid ""
"Ruvio insisted on leaving all Akladians in our army outside the city, in the "
"forest, but I refused. Of course, the inhabitants of Freetown weren't eager "
"to let Akladians into their city. But there were no serious incidents, much "
"to Ruvio's surprise."
msgstr ""
"Ruvio voulait qu'on laisse tous les Akladiens de notre armée en dehors de la "
"cité, dans la forêt. Mais je refusai. Bien sûr les habitants de Freetown "
"n'avaient aucune envie de voir des soldats Akladiens entrer dans leur ville. "
"Mais, à la grande surprise de Ruvio, il n'y eut aucun incident sérieux."

#. [part]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/15_Back_in_Freetown.cfg:33
msgid ""
"Huon and Mithrandil returned a few days after our arrival. When the time "
"appointed for our next meeting came, nobody questioned my right to be there. "
"Lorin also insisted on participating and, after a short quarrel, Gwidle, the "
"most respected leader of the people of Freetown, agreed."
msgstr ""
"Huon et Mithrandil furent de retour quelques jours après notre arrivée. "
"Quand le moment d'une nouvelle réunion fut venu, personne ne remit en cause "
"mon droit à y assister. Lorin insista aussi pour participer, et après une "
"courte querelle, Gwidle, le chef le plus respecté du peuple de Freetown "
"accepta."

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/15_Back_in_Freetown.cfg:146
msgid ""
"Greetings and wishes of long life and luck for everyone, even for those who "
"were not invited here and who really should never have entered this city. "
"Mithrandil, you were one who insisted on this gathering, so please, begin."
msgstr ""
"Salutations et voeux de longue vie et de chance à tous, même à ceux qui "
"n'étaient pas invités et qui n'auraient jamais dû entrer dans cette cité. "
"Mithrandil, vous êtes celui qui a demandé cette rencontre, alors commencez "
"s'il vous plaît."

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/15_Back_in_Freetown.cfg:147
msgid ""
"Yes, indeed. The news brought here by Ruvio and this brave young man is "
"quite important."
msgstr ""
"Oui, en effet. Les nouvelles apportées par Ruvio et par ce courageux jeune "
"homme sont plutôt importantes."

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/15_Back_in_Freetown.cfg:148
msgid ""
"But why? All they brought back is a name: Grekulak.  What's so important "
"about that?"
msgstr ""
"Mais pourquoi ? Tout ce qu'ils appris c'est ce nom : Grekulak. Pourquoi est-"
"ce si important ?"

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/15_Back_in_Freetown.cfg:149
msgid ""
"I think everyone here knows the legends about Wesnoth's past. When our "
"kingdom was powerful and rich. You may also recall the old story about the "
"invasion by evil forces from the east, led by the evil lich, Mal-Ravanal."
msgstr ""
"Je pense que tout le monde ici connaît les légendes du passé de Wesnoth. "
"Quand ce royaume était riche et en paix. Vous connaissez aussi la vieille "
"histoire de l'invasion des forces maléfiques de l'est, dirigées par la "
"liche, Mal-Ravanal."

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/15_Back_in_Freetown.cfg:150
msgid ""
"What? Of course not, that would be a legend from WESNOTHIAN culture.  Is "
"this yet another fairy tale?"
msgstr ""
"Quoi ? Bien sûr que non, il doit s'agir d'une légende de la culture "
"WESNOTHIENNE. C'est encore un conte de fées ?"

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/15_Back_in_Freetown.cfg:151
msgid ""
"During this invasion, large parts of Wesnoth were turned into barren "
"wasteland. The swamps of Saorduc were vast, fertile lands a mere three "
"hundred years ago. But this was before a civil war that left Wesnoth divided."
msgstr ""
"Après cette invasion, une grande partie de Wesnoth devint un désert stérile. "
"Les marais de Saorduc étaient une vaste terre fertile il y a à peu près "
"trois cents ans. Mais, c'était avant la guerre civile et la division de "
"Wesnoth."

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/15_Back_in_Freetown.cfg:152
msgid ""
"Yes, we know this story. That's why the Akladians were able to conquer us... "
"we were splintered. They could never have been succesful had we been united."
msgstr ""
"Oui, nous connaissons cette histoire. C'est pourquoi les Akladiens ont pu "
"nous conquérir... nous étions éparpillés. Ils n'auraient sans doute jamais "
"réussi si nous avions été unis."

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/15_Back_in_Freetown.cfg:153
msgid ""
"We won because this land was given to us by God. That's why he divided you "
"and made you forget how to handle swords, why you became weak. When we came, "
"mercenaries were doing all the fighting for you."
msgstr ""
"Nous avons gagné parce que cette terre nous a été donnée par Dieu. Voila "
"pourquoi il vous a divisé et vous a fait oublier comment on tient une épée, "
"ce qui vous a rendu faibles. Quand nous sommes arrivés, c'étaient seulement "
"des mercenaires qui se battaient chez vous."

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/15_Back_in_Freetown.cfg:154
msgid ""
"So, as I was saying before you were so kind as to interrupt me, some time "
"ago a new leader appeared amongst the orcs. His name was Grekulak. He united "
"orcish tribes, one by one, using treachery and gold.  Right now he rules "
"more than a third of the orcish hordes."
msgstr ""
"Donc, comme je le disais juste avant que vous soyez assez aimable pour "
"m'interrompre, il y a quelque temps, un nouveau chef est apparu parmi les "
"orcs. Son nom est Grekulak. Il a uni les tribus, une par une, par traîtrise "
"ou par corruption. En ce moment, il dirige plus d'un tiers des hordes orcs."

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/15_Back_in_Freetown.cfg:155
msgid ""
"Wait, wait. You were talking about Mal-Ravanal. What does he have to do with "
"Grekulak?"
msgstr ""
"Attendez, attendez. Vous nous parliez de Mal-Ravanal. Qu'est-ce qu'il a à "
"voir avec ce Grekulak ?"

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/15_Back_in_Freetown.cfg:156
msgid ""
"We believe that Grekulak is one of the last surviving adepts of Mal-Ravanal. "
"We suspected that he was behind the sudden alliance of orcs and Akladians. "
"Now we are certain. We are also sure that this orcish invasion is just the "
"beginning."
msgstr ""
"Nous pensons que Grekulak est un des adeptes survivants de Mal-Ravanal. Nous "
"soupçonnions qu'il était derrière l'alliance soudaine des orcs et des "
"Akladiens. Maintenant, nous en sommes sûrs. Nous sommes aussi sûrs que cette "
"invasion orc n'est qu'un début."

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/15_Back_in_Freetown.cfg:158
msgid ""
"I mean you will face a full-scale invasion soon. An undead army, orcs, and "
"who-knows-what else. You will need help from the mages."
msgstr ""
"Je veux dire que bientôt, vous allez devoir faire face à une invasion de "
"grande envergure. Une armée de morts-vivants, d'orcs et de Dieu-sait-quoi "
"d'autre. Vous allez avoir besoin de l'aide des mages."

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/15_Back_in_Freetown.cfg:159
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "Great. Akladians, orcs, zombies... and we need the help of the mages. I "
#| "imagine that, being a wise elf and all, you know of course that no mages "
#| "exist anymore. Maybe a few on the Isle of Anduin, or in besieged "
#| "Elensefar, but not enough to help us."
msgid ""
"Great. Akladians, orcs, zombies... and we need the help of the mages. I "
"imagine that, being a wise elf and all, you know of course that no mages "
"exist anymore. Maybe a few on the Isle of Alduin, or in besieged Elensefar, "
"but not enough to help us."
msgstr ""
"Magnifique. Des Akladiens, des orcs, des zombies et nous avons besoin de "
"l'aide des mages ! Mais puisque vous êtes un elfe sage comme tout, vous "
"savez bien sûr que les mages n'existent plus. Il en reste peut-être quelques "
"uns sur l'île d'Anduin, ou assiégés à Elensefar, mais pas assez pour nous "
"aider."

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/15_Back_in_Freetown.cfg:160
msgid ""
"Actually, I'm pretty sure that Mithrandil is thinking about ONE specific "
"mage. Am I correct?"
msgstr ""
"Je crois plutôt que Mithrandil pense plus précisément à UN mage en "
"particulier. J'ai raison ?"

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/15_Back_in_Freetown.cfg:161
msgid ""
"Yes. Deorien. A white mage, living somewhere in eastern Wesnoth. You should "
"go and find him. I will give you my soldiers and even gold, if you want. "
"This should be all I need to tell you for now."
msgstr ""
"Oui, Deorien. Un mage blanc, qui vit quelque part à l'est de Wesnoth. Vous "
"devriez aller le trouver. Je vous donnerai mes soldats et même de l'or si "
"vous voulez. C'est tout ce que j'ai besoin de vous dire pour l'instant."

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/15_Back_in_Freetown.cfg:162
msgid ""
"Then this meeting is adjourned. Take the evening to ponder this counsel, and "
"we will re-convene and discuss everything on the morrow."
msgstr ""
"Donc cette rencontre est ajournée. Prenez la soirée pour peser ces conseils "
"et nous reparlerons de tout cela demain matin."

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/15_Back_in_Freetown.cfg:174
msgid ""
"Great. The green devils advise us to seek the help of those who are a blight "
"on the face of God's world. The MAGES."
msgstr ""
"Génial. Les démons verts nous conseillent d'aller chercher l'aide de gens "
"qui ne sont que de la poussière à la surface du monde de Dieu, les MAGES."

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/15_Back_in_Freetown.cfg:175
msgid ""
"You often speak about something you call God, Lorin. Can you tell us more "
"about your God?"
msgstr ""
"Vous parlez souvent de quelque chose que vous appelez Dieu, Lorin. Pouvez-"
"vous nous en dire un peu plus sur votre Dieu ?"

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/15_Back_in_Freetown.cfg:176
msgid ""
"He is the force behind the universe. He created the world and is our father. "
"He gave us the world to rule. One of his angels tried to stop us from doing "
"that, deceiving us and trying to imprison us in his garden, but a messiah "
"came from the Hagarthen clan. He told us that God desired us to wait no "
"more..."
msgstr ""
"Il est la force qui tient l'univers. Il a créé le monde et il est notre "
"père. Il nous a donné le monde à diriger. Un de ses anges essaya de nous en "
"empêcher en nous trompant et en nous emprisonnant dans son jardin, mais un "
"messie vint du clan Hagarthen et il nous dit que Dieu ne voulait pas que "
"nous attendions plus..."

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/15_Back_in_Freetown.cfg:177
msgid ""
"So we killed that evil angel and his minions to journey west. We fought our "
"way through the deserts and the swamps, fighting with nightmarish creatures, "
"not to mention lizards and green elves. I was raised hearing songs about "
"this epic journey."
msgstr ""
"Donc nous avons tué cet ange malfaisant et ses sous-fifres et nous sommes "
"partis vers l'ouest. Nous trouvâmes notre chemin dans les marais et les "
"collines en bataillant avec des créatures de cauchemars, sans parler des "
"lézards et des elfes verts. J'ai grandi en écoutant les chansons qui "
"parlaient de ce voyage épique."

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/15_Back_in_Freetown.cfg:178
msgid ""
"Finally, we reached Wesnoth, our people decimated but hardened because it "
"was the wish of God that our weak should perish before we began our holy "
"task. When we came from the east the underling armies were like dust before "
"a wind. We conquered Wesnoth. Well, almost."
msgstr ""
"Finalement, nous atteignîmes Wesnoth, décimés mais endurcis, parce que "
"c'était la volonté de Dieu que les faibles périssent avant que nous ne "
"commencions notre sainte tâche. Quand nous sommes arrivés de l'est, les "
"armées des métèques ont été balayées comme poussière dans le vent. Nous "
"avons conquis Wesnoth. Enfin, presque."

#. [event]
#: A_New_Order/scenarios/15_Back_in_Freetown.cfg:179
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "As for mages, they  are main opponents of God in his fight for the good "
#| "of the universe, attempting to usurp his powers for themselves. Elves are "
#| "minions of the fallen angels. They are to be exterminated."
msgid ""
"As for mages, they are the main adversaries of God in his fight for the good "
"of the universe, attempting to usurp his powers for themselves. Elves are "
"minions of the fallen angels. They are to be exterminated."
msgstr ""
"Quant aux mages, ce sont les adversaires principaux de Dieu dans son combat "
